            Scale of Election Expenses (Municipal Councils) Order 1994</docTitle><enactingFormula role="empoweringSection">(<ref href="/hk/cap554/s45">Cap. 554, section
                45</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><commencementNote>[11 November 1994]</commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2019/er2">E.R. 2 of 2019</ref>)</sourceNote><editorialNote type="footnote" id="ID_1553237398711_001">
            <content>Editorial Note: </content>
            <content>This Order was originally made under the Corrupt and Illegal Practices
                Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap288">Cap. 288</ref>). Though that Ordinance was
                repealed, this Order continues in force so far as it is not inconsistent with the
                Elections (Corrupt and Illegal Conduct) Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap554">Cap.
                    554</ref>) and has the effect for all purposes as if made under <ref href="/hk/cap554">Cap. 554</ref>. (See
                    <ref href="/hk/cap554/s48">section
                    48 of Cap. 554</ref>)</content>
        </editorialNote><section id="ID_1438403433789_001" name="s1" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><heading>Application</heading><content>This Order shall apply to elections for geographical constituencies of the Urban
            Council and the Regional Council to be held on or after 5 March 1995.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403433851_002" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2019-06-20" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Maximum scale of election expenses</heading><content>For the purposes of <ref>section 13(1)</ref> of the
            Ordinance*,
            the maximum scale of election expenses that may be incurred by or on behalf of a
            candidate in respect of election to a geographical constituency of the Urban Council or
            the Regional Council shall be $100,000.</content><sourceNote>(<ref href="/hk/1994/ln666">L.N. 666 of 1994</ref>)</sourceNote><editorialNote type="footnote" id="ID_1553237936457_001">
